title: Bob Dylan at Carnegie Chapter Hall 1961 (recently circulated tap
description:
Bob Dylan gave his first concert as a headliner at Carnegie Chapter Hall in New York City on November 4, 1961. The concert was organized by Izzy Young and Dylan advertised it when he appeared on Oscar Brand\\\&#039;s radio show, but only 54 people paid for tickets and Izzy Young lost money, but he also made history. A few years later, Dylan would sell out far larger concert halls and he keeps on performing 47 years later.
A tape of the firat seven songs from this concert has been available for decades and \\\"This Land Is Your Land\\\" appeared on the \\\"No Direction Home\\\" soundtrack, but this 15-song tape started circulating just a few weeks ago. It\\\&#039;s an important find.
The sound quality is mostly very good, but remember that this is a bootleg recording, not an official release. The sound quality on some tracks is uneven.
The bitrate is quite low, but these files are identical to the files I received from a collector and this recording is to the best of my knowledge not currently circulating in better quality.
